41:20.769 --> 41:22.688
Feel good, huh?

41:24.189 --> 41:26.692
Harder.

41:26.733 --> 41:28.735
You like that?

41:28.777 --> 41:31.697
Oh, God.

41:31.738 --> 41:33.240
You like that, girl?

41:33.281 --> 41:34.658
Yeah. Yeah?

41:34.700 --> 41:39.037
Oh! Oh, yeah.

41:39.079 --> 41:41.039
You like it harder?

41:41.081 --> 41:44.543
Oh, yeah.

41:44.584 --> 41:47.212
Do you like it rough?
Oh, God, yeah.

41:47.254 --> 41:50.215
Give it to me now.
Give it to me, cowboy.

41:50.257 --> 41:54.761
♪ It's now or never... ♪

41:54.803 --> 41:56.263
My name ain't cowboy.

42:30.589 --> 42:33.300
So, with a serious problem like that,
if you don't act like a gentleman...

42:33.341 --> 42:35.302
Hey, I thought that was
your truck outside.

42:35.343 --> 42:37.763
Hey, hey. Clay, how are you,
man? I'm good. How you doin'?

42:37.804 --> 42:40.057
Good to see you,
you son of a bitch. Good.

42:40.098 --> 42:42.726
- You're up awfully early.
- Yeah. I gotta get a lot of miles in today.

42:42.768 --> 42:46.396
Oh, yeah?
On the road again, huh?

42:46.438 --> 42:48.482
Mm-hmm.

42:51.109 --> 42:52.778
So, uh, how's Amanda?

42:54.112 --> 42:55.906
Man, you sure
were right about her, boy.

42:55.947 --> 42:59.785
- She was a mouthy little bitch.
- I tried to tell you.

42:59.826 --> 43:02.287
- You should've heard some of the things she said about you.
- What kind of things?

43:02.329 --> 43:05.999
I don't think you'd
believe 'em if I told you.

43:06.041 --> 43:09.503
Uh, Kimberly? Kimberly? I'm
ready for the check when you are.

43:09.544 --> 43:13.215
No rush. Appreciate it.

43:13.256 --> 43:15.342
Don't worry about it though. I'm
not going to say anything to anybody.

43:15.383 --> 43:17.135
Just between us, brother.

43:17.177 --> 43:18.929
There you go.

43:18.970 --> 43:20.472
Thank you, girl. Hey, Clay.

43:20.514 --> 43:22.307
- Hi, Kimberly. How are you?
- Good.

43:22.349 --> 43:25.268
Well, I guess you two are
already acquainted then, huh?

43:25.310 --> 43:28.021
He used to babysit me
when I was younger.

43:28.063 --> 43:30.774
Is that right?

43:30.816 --> 43:33.151
Used to babysit you?
That's great.

43:33.193 --> 43:36.822
Well, I think this should
settle us up.

43:36.863 --> 43:39.157
- You keep the change.
- Thanks.

43:39.199 --> 43:40.742
You deserve it.

43:40.784 --> 43:42.786
You thank yourself. Thank you.

43:42.828 --> 43:46.456
- And could I get a cup of coffee?
- Sure.

43:46.498 --> 43:50.127
Okay, thanks. Thank you, girl.

43:50.168 --> 43:51.753
Mm, mm, mm, mm, mm.

43:51.795 --> 43:54.631
Hey. She's just a kid.

43:54.673 --> 43:59.427
Yeah. Whatever you say, man.

44:02.222 --> 44:03.598
I want to thank you again, Clay.

44:03.598 --> 44:05.142
Yeah? For what?

44:05.183 --> 44:09.563
That thing at the lake...

44:09.604 --> 44:12.315
used to be friends would stick
their neck out for each other.

44:12.357 --> 44:16.361
Not so much anymore,
you know what I mean?

44:16.403 --> 44:19.865
- Well, it was no big deal.
- Hell it isn't a big deal.

44:19.906 --> 44:22.617
I wanna let you know that
I really appreciate it, Clay.

44:24.327 --> 44:25.871
All right.

44:25.912 --> 44:27.330
'Nough said.

44:27.372 --> 44:28.748
- All right.
- All right.

44:28.790 --> 44:31.751
All right, man.
A lotta miles on this one today.

44:31.793 --> 44:33.503
See you later.

44:41.344 --> 44:42.929
♪ ♪

45:44.074 --> 45:45.700
What happened?

45:45.700 --> 45:47.577
Somebody got killed.

46:03.927 --> 46:05.679
I'm sorry, Clay.
You can't come any further.

46:05.720 --> 46:06.972
What happened?

46:07.013 --> 46:10.267
It's Amanda. What?

46:10.308 --> 46:15.063
Somebody cut her all to pieces.

46:16.564 --> 46:18.108
Oh.

46:24.698 --> 46:26.324
- ♪ Bom, bom, bom, bom ♪
- ♪ Why, baby, why ♪

46:32.622 --> 46:35.792
♪ Why, baby, why
don't you need me ♪

46:35.834 --> 46:37.168
♪ Why, baby, why ♪

46:37.210 --> 46:39.504
♪ Like I needed you ♪

46:39.546 --> 46:41.214
You're late!

46:41.256 --> 46:44.634
♪ If you need love
and affection ♪

46:44.676 --> 46:48.263
♪ Come to my lovin' arms ♪

46:48.305 --> 46:50.056
♪ Why, baby, why ♪

46:50.098 --> 46:53.018
♪ I'll be your shield
for protection ♪

46:53.059 --> 46:57.981
- ♪ Why, baby, why ♪
- ♪ I won't do you no harm ♪

46:58.023 --> 47:02.193
♪ There will be no trouble
and strife ♪

47:02.235 --> 47:07.991
♪ I'll be your slave
the rest of my life ♪

47:16.791 --> 47:20.211
I don't know
what to tell you, Dan.

47:21.921 --> 47:24.132
I've never seen anything
like this before.

47:28.762 --> 47:32.223
Agent Shelby.

47:32.265 --> 47:35.435
- Hi. Are you Sheriff Mooney?
- Yeah.

47:35.477 --> 47:36.770
How you doing? Dale Shelby, FBI.

47:36.811 --> 47:38.438
This is Agent Reynard.

47:38.480 --> 47:40.565
May we see the body, please?

47:53.286 --> 47:56.206
When was she discovered?

47:56.247 --> 47:58.625
A couple hours ago.

47:58.666 --> 48:00.835
Meter man saw her.

48:00.835 --> 48:03.755
Meter's right outside
the window.

48:03.797 --> 48:06.174
Has the weapon been recovered?

48:06.216 --> 48:07.801
No.

48:07.842 --> 48:10.470
Hey, Sher.

48:10.512 --> 48:12.180
Oh, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

48:12.222 --> 48:14.849
You're standing in evidence.

48:14.849 --> 48:17.143
God.

48:23.566 --> 48:25.026
Hey.

48:25.068 --> 48:26.319
Uh, there's a really big crowd
out there.

48:26.361 --> 48:28.363
You want me to run 'em off?

48:28.405 --> 48:30.698
Just keep them off the property.

48:30.740 --> 48:35.161
- Okay, Barney?
- Yes, sir, Sheriff.

48:36.454 --> 48:39.707
Your deputy's name is Barney?

48:39.749 --> 48:42.252
Yeah.

48:42.293 --> 48:44.587
That's great.

48:54.848 --> 48:56.641
Excuse me, excuse me.

48:56.683 --> 48:59.269
Who are all these people?

48:59.310 --> 49:02.814
Well, they're
the state police...

49:02.856 --> 49:05.358
the fire chief, and...

49:05.400 --> 49:06.693
a couple of councilmen.

49:06.734 --> 49:08.987
Why is the fire chief here?

49:09.028 --> 49:11.197
Well, he's done
some police work before.

49:11.239 --> 49:12.615
I thought it couldn't hurt.

49:12.657 --> 49:15.493
And how about the councilmen?

49:15.535 --> 49:17.996
Well, uh...

49:18.037 --> 49:20.039
they wanted to come.

49:20.081 --> 49:23.001
You know, ordinarily,
I say the more the merrier.

49:23.042 --> 49:25.170
I do. I say it all the time.

49:25.211 --> 49:28.006
But, uh, a murder scene
is not really crowd appropriate.

49:28.047 --> 49:32.427
So could we just make sure
that nobody touches anything?

49:32.469 --> 49:36.264
Thank you so much.

49:38.308 --> 49:42.103
Anybody seen this?

49:42.145 --> 49:43.688
No.

49:43.730 --> 49:47.525
- What do you suppose...
- He cleaned up afterwards.

49:53.823 --> 49:55.492
Bingo.

50:05.418 --> 50:07.795
Mm-hmm.

50:18.681 --> 50:20.975
How well did you know Amanda?

50:20.975 --> 50:22.560
Pretty well.

50:22.602 --> 50:23.978
What was she like?

50:23.978 --> 50:25.855
Honest.

50:25.897 --> 50:27.857
Meaning?

50:27.899 --> 50:31.819
Amanda wasn't the nicest
person in the world.

50:54.509 --> 50:57.971
I told Dr. Jaffe
to meet us here.

51:21.661 --> 51:23.663
Did you catch somebody?

51:28.876 --> 51:31.212
The wounds were all made
with the same knife,

51:31.254 --> 51:33.339
probably a standard
kitchen knife.

51:33.381 --> 51:35.341
The fatal blow entered
just below the shoulder blade

51:35.383 --> 51:40.555
where it pierced her heart
and her left lung.

51:40.597 --> 51:42.682
How long has her husband
been dead?

51:42.724 --> 51:45.059
Oh, about a month.

51:45.059 --> 51:47.186
Has she been seeing anyone
since that time?

51:47.228 --> 51:49.564
Not that I know of.

51:49.606 --> 51:53.067
Excuse me.
Any signs of sexual assault?

51:53.067 --> 51:56.112
No. But she did have intercourse
within two hours of her death.

51:56.154 --> 51:58.364
How many of the wounds
were postmortem?

51:58.406 --> 52:00.074
Almost all of them.

52:00.074 --> 52:03.828
I counted more than 40 points
of entry in all.

52:04.996 --> 52:07.498
Let me show you.

52:16.591 --> 52:19.218
The first thing that
I'm gonna do when I get back

52:19.260 --> 52:21.429
is to get some decent food.

52:24.474 --> 52:26.184
I've tasted better,
you know what I'm saying?

52:30.688 --> 52:32.899
You pound down the stuff
like there's no tomorrow.

52:32.940 --> 52:34.525
Uh-huh.

52:34.567 --> 52:38.696
Now you know what it's made of.

52:38.738 --> 52:40.490
I don't wanna talk
about what it's made of.

52:40.531 --> 52:44.202
I'm eating this.

52:54.128 --> 52:55.838
Small cheese pie.

52:55.880 --> 52:58.257
- Okay, what do I owe you?
- Uh, 7.50.

53:12.855 --> 53:14.649
Whatever floats your boat.

53:14.691 --> 53:16.109
Keep it.

53:16.150 --> 53:18.111
Oh, thanks.

53:29.831 --> 53:31.666
<i>Ah, Go...</i>

53:47.056 --> 53:48.891
Why don't you start
by describing

53:48.933 --> 53:50.435
your relationship with Amanda?

53:50.476 --> 53:53.187
- We were friends.
- Nothing more?

53:53.187 --> 53:54.647
No.

54:04.741 --> 54:06.784
Do you like movies, Clay?

54:08.745 --> 54:10.705
And can I call you Clay?

54:10.747 --> 54:12.373
Sure.

54:12.415 --> 54:15.626
Sure you like movies,
or sure I can call you Clay?

54:15.668 --> 54:19.130
Sure you can call me Clay,
and I like movies.

54:19.172 --> 54:21.215
I mean, you got to living
in a town like this, right?

54:23.509 --> 54:25.219
Amanda was quite a fan too.
Did you know that?

54:26.637 --> 54:28.139
No, I didn't.

54:28.181 --> 54:30.183
She had a very extensive
video collection.

54:30.224 --> 54:33.269
Most of the stuff
was not really my taste.

54:33.311 --> 54:35.980
Low-brow comedies, action junk,

54:36.022 --> 54:38.149
things of that nature.

54:38.191 --> 54:41.569
But I was very bored in my motel room,
so I decided to borrow one of her videos.

54:41.611 --> 54:45.114
- You ever seen Alien?
- I think so, a long time ago.

54:45.156 --> 54:47.408
It's a great flick.
Very empowering.

54:47.450 --> 54:49.911
Although small screen, shitty dub,
is not really the way to experience it.

54:49.952 --> 54:54.165
But I was just watching it,
minding my own business, and guess what happened.

54:56.209 --> 54:59.378
Let's find out.

55:11.557 --> 55:13.142
Oh, God!

55:26.364 --> 55:28.616
So you're a full-service
garage, eh?

55:32.453 --> 55:34.372
That was really impressive,
Mr. DeMille.

55:34.413 --> 55:36.207
When did you shoot that?

55:37.959 --> 55:40.753
A couple of months ago. Yeah.

55:40.795 --> 55:42.588
She said she was gonna
record over it,

55:42.630 --> 55:44.590
but I guess she didn't.

55:44.632 --> 55:47.009
No.

55:54.851 --> 55:57.186
Why didn't you tell me
about you two?

55:57.228 --> 56:01.232
We were having an affair,
Mooney.

56:01.274 --> 56:03.901
That's not the kind of thing
you talk about.

56:05.319 --> 56:07.196
What do you know
about Carol Pierce?

56:11.325 --> 56:13.411
Who's Carol Pierce?

56:15.162 --> 56:17.665
The woman whose body you found
floating in Bear Lake.

56:20.918 --> 56:22.962
I've never heard
the name before.

56:23.004 --> 56:25.172
She's been missing about two,
two and a half months.

56:25.214 --> 56:27.174
She was last seen
in the Great Falls area.

56:27.216 --> 56:30.595
Do you ever get up there
for any reason? Great Falls.

56:31.929 --> 56:33.764
Wait a minute.

56:33.806 --> 56:35.725
Mooney, what's she trying to do?

56:35.766 --> 56:38.519
I'm not trying to do anything.
I'm trying to tell you something.

56:38.561 --> 56:40.646
She was stabbed...
Just like Amanda...

56:40.688 --> 56:42.690
and just like
seven other women...

56:42.732 --> 56:45.359
who have turned up dead in
this state over the last two years.

56:45.359 --> 56:48.112
We've also got five women missing,
including Gloria Collins.

56:48.154 --> 56:49.906
So why don't you quit
dicking around...

56:49.947 --> 56:51.574
and tell me
what you know about her?

56:51.616 --> 56:54.160
This is crazy. This
is really fucking crazy.

56:54.201 --> 56:56.579
Mooney, tell her
that this is crazy.

56:58.289 --> 57:01.208
You were the last person
to be seen with her.

57:01.250 --> 57:03.502
I'm not answering
any more questions.

57:03.544 --> 57:06.756
- You got to admit it's a big coincidence.
- What?

57:06.797 --> 57:09.425
You're sleeping with one victim,
you're dating another,

57:09.467 --> 57:11.802
and you actually found a third.

57:13.721 --> 57:15.139
Come on.

57:17.850 --> 57:19.602
We're a little curious.

57:19.644 --> 57:22.313
You know, I'm not
talking anymore.

57:22.355 --> 57:23.981
All right, Mooney,
I want a lawyer.

57:26.067 --> 57:28.486
You don't need a lawyer, Clay.

57:28.527 --> 57:30.529
You're not being charged
with anything.

57:30.571 --> 57:34.742
But I do think you can help us.

57:34.784 --> 57:38.579
There's bound to be
something you saw or heard...

57:38.621 --> 57:40.748
that might lead us
to the killer.

57:55.012 --> 57:57.682
Look, why don't you go on home
and think about it.

57:59.517 --> 58:02.228
Maybe you're
forgetting something.

58:02.269 --> 58:04.981
If anything comes to you,

58:05.022 --> 58:06.691
you give me a call.

58:17.201 --> 58:20.246
Hey, Mooney? Do me a favor?

58:20.287 --> 58:23.124
You make sure that tape
doesn't get out. Okay?

58:23.165 --> 58:25.334
You've got my word.

58:36.220 --> 58:38.264
He's not your man.

58:38.305 --> 58:39.807
Why?

58:39.849 --> 58:42.810
Let me ask you something.

58:42.852 --> 58:46.647
Why would he lead us
to one of the bodies?

58:46.689 --> 58:48.649
That doesn't make any sense.

58:48.691 --> 58:50.943
We're not talking
about rational thought here.

58:50.985 --> 58:52.570
Sometimes people
want to be caught.

58:52.611 --> 58:54.113
Sometimes they're
crying out for help.

58:54.155 --> 58:56.198
Sometimes they push the envelopes,
they taunt us.

58:56.240 --> 58:57.575
No.

58:57.616 --> 58:59.493
Clay is a nice guy.

59:00.995 --> 59:04.415
They're all... nice guys.

59:14.050 --> 59:15.676
Hello?

59:15.718 --> 59:17.678
Hey, buddy.

59:17.720 --> 59:19.221
Lester.

59:19.263 --> 59:21.057
Yeah, one and the same.

59:21.098 --> 59:23.893
Listen,
Clay. I think me and you should get together.

59:25.811 --> 59:27.271
Hello?

59:27.313 --> 59:29.815
- Are you there?
- Clayborne?

59:29.857 --> 59:31.692
Y-Yeah, I'm here.

59:31.734 --> 59:34.487
Listen,
I'm gonna be up your way later on tonight.

59:34.528 --> 59:35.780
So where's a place
me and you can meet?

59:35.821 --> 59:37.490
You know, something comfortable.

59:37.531 --> 59:40.743
Um, what about Doc Holiday's?

59:40.785 --> 59:42.244
Oh.

59:42.286 --> 59:45.081
No, I don't think so, Clay.

59:45.122 --> 59:48.084
You know,
I don't think me and you should be seen together.

59:48.125 --> 59:49.543
Do you?

01:00:08.145 --> 01:00:09.980
Hey, Clay.

01:00:11.816 --> 01:00:14.235
I didn't think you'd show.

01:00:15.736 --> 01:00:18.155
Just had to make sure that...

01:00:18.197 --> 01:00:20.116
you weren't followed, my man.

01:00:21.450 --> 01:00:23.452
Huh.

01:00:23.494 --> 01:00:25.955
Boy, don't this
bring back memories?

01:00:28.833 --> 01:00:30.292
Why? Why? Easy,
buddy! Easy, buddy!

01:00:30.334 --> 01:00:32.378
Don't get all riled
up on me now! Why?

01:00:32.419 --> 01:00:35.131
Don't get riled up on me now,
boy! Get your fuckin'...

01:00:35.172 --> 01:00:37.383
Go slow, son. Take it slow.

01:00:37.424 --> 01:00:38.884
Take it slow.

01:00:38.926 --> 01:00:42.346
Take your ass slow, boy.
I told you now.

01:00:42.388 --> 01:00:44.390
Play nice
with your big daddy here.

01:00:44.431 --> 01:00:46.225
Why?

01:00:46.267 --> 01:00:48.394
Why? I was doing
you a goddamn favor.

01:00:48.435 --> 01:00:50.020
I never asked you
to fucking kill her!

01:00:50.062 --> 01:00:51.564
Well, you're not sorry
she's gone, are you?

01:00:51.605 --> 01:00:53.566
They think I did it.

01:00:53.607 --> 01:00:55.609
No,
they don't. They think I did all of 'em.

01:00:58.112 --> 01:01:01.198
They don't have nothing on you.

01:01:01.240 --> 01:01:03.576
It'll all blow over in a week.

01:01:03.617 --> 01:01:05.578
Jesus Christ.

01:01:05.619 --> 01:01:07.913
Bring down the
temperature a little bit.

01:01:07.955 --> 01:01:12.001
It won't take that long
if I tell them about you.

01:01:12.042 --> 01:01:14.461
- But you won't do that.
- Yeah? Why not?

01:01:14.503 --> 01:01:17.214
Well, you already
had your chance, Clay.

01:01:18.799 --> 01:01:20.718
But you didn't do it, did you?

01:01:22.636 --> 01:01:26.640
I think you're a little worried
about what old Amanda told me.

01:01:31.979 --> 01:01:35.316
I mean, here you got
two guys fishing,

01:01:35.357 --> 01:01:37.902
and then out of
the middle of nowhere,

01:01:37.943 --> 01:01:41.405
all of a sudden,
a body washes up?

01:01:41.447 --> 01:01:44.992
That's not the kind of
thing you see every day.

01:01:45.034 --> 01:01:49.246
But yet, neither of us seemed
all that surprised by it, man.

01:01:51.040 --> 01:01:53.042
You know,
what I can't understand...

01:01:53.083 --> 01:01:55.669
is how come, after
you dropped me off,

01:01:55.669 --> 01:01:57.880
you didn't just
come back here...

01:01:57.922 --> 01:02:00.633
and throw her ass
right back in the lake.

01:02:00.674 --> 01:02:02.760
Nobody would have
known. I didn't kill her.

01:02:02.801 --> 01:02:05.846
I believe you. I
said it. I believe you.

01:02:05.888 --> 01:02:07.306
I believe you, Clay.

01:02:07.348 --> 01:02:10.142
But I don't think
that anybody else would.

01:02:10.184 --> 01:02:12.186
How many have there been?

01:02:12.228 --> 01:02:14.355
Oh, come on now, Clay.

01:02:14.396 --> 01:02:17.691
Oh, let's not get
into that shit.

01:02:17.691 --> 01:02:19.568
I want to know.

01:02:25.199 --> 01:02:28.702
You wouldn't be trying to play
detective or anything with me, would you?

01:02:30.204 --> 01:02:32.498
You know if I go down,
you go with me.

01:02:32.539 --> 01:02:34.917
So why not tell me?

01:02:34.959 --> 01:02:37.920
Well, there's a few
they don't know about.

01:02:39.838 --> 01:02:42.925
But that's just
the way it is, Clay.

01:02:42.967 --> 01:02:45.678
Some people can just, uh,

01:02:45.719 --> 01:02:47.513
disappear.

01:02:47.554 --> 01:02:50.349
Nobody misses 'em.

01:02:50.391 --> 01:02:53.018
What, Mama Lester
didn't love you?

01:02:53.060 --> 01:02:54.395
Don't lower yourself.

01:02:54.436 --> 01:02:58.190
Don't lower it!
Don't lower yourself!

01:02:58.232 --> 01:03:00.567
Seems to me like you're the
last person in the goddamn world...

01:03:00.609 --> 01:03:03.696
that should be asking me
a fuckin' question like that.

